# Trivy suppressions — each entry is a deliberate, reviewed decision, not a
# blanket mute. Vulnerability and secret findings are never suppressed here.

# DS-0002: "run as a non-root USER". The runtime image intentionally starts as
# root today because the persisted data directories (/uploads, /backups) are
# bind/named volumes that existing self-hosted deployments created under root;
# switching the container to a non-root UID would make those volumes
# unwritable on upgrade until the operator ran a one-time chown. Running as
# non-root is planned as a coordinated change shipped with an upgrade/migration
# note, not slipped into a patch. Tracked for a future release.
DS-0002
